                                                                <div class="text">
                                                                    <div itemprop="text">
                                                                        <p>Calling a bread roll a &ldquo;biscuit&rdquo; really takes the biscuit. The word comes from French, meaning &ldquo;twice cooked&rdquo; (bis &ndash; cuit). Are bread rolls twice cooked? Of course modern biscuits aren&rsquo;t twice cooked either but they were originally.</p>
                                                                        <p>As far as I know no Briton calls a bread roll a pudding, though we do call them lots of other things in different parts of the country, e.g. Baps, Stotties, Buns, Rolls, Bin Lids, Cobs, Batches, Bulkies, Barms, Teacakes, Butties, Nudgers and Blaas (not a complete list).</p>
